Here's a `ProductDetailViewModel` using the CommunityToolkit.Mvvm source generators for clean, binding-ready code:

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace YourApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isBusy;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        if (IsBusy) return;

        try
        {
            IsBusy = true;

            // Replace with your actual data service call
            await Task.Delay(500);

            Name = "Widget Pro";
            Price = 29.99m;
            IsAvailable = true;
        }
        finally
        {
            IsBusy = false;
        }
    }
}
```

**How it works:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` generates public properties (`Name`, `Price`, etc.) with `INotifyPropertyChanged` calls — bindings update automatically.
- `[RelayCommand]` generates a `LoadCommand` (IAsyncRelayCommand) from the `LoadAsync` method.
- `IsBusy` prevents duplicate calls and can drive an `ActivityIndicator`.

**XAML usage:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <VerticalStackLayout>
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='{0:C}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding IsBusy}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Required NuGet:** `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (≥ 8.0).
